//*
//* RESNAME RULES RELATED DDNAMES
//* - RACF COMMANDS AND LISTINGS ARE BASED ON RESNAME_RULE PROCESSING
//*
//RESPRINT   DD SYSOUT=*   * PRINT RESNAME_RULE CONTROL STATEMENTS
//RESRULEA   DD SYSOUT=*   * RACF RESNAME CHANGES
//RESRULED   DD SYSOUT=*   * RACF RDELETE
//RESRULEF   DD SYSOUT=*   * RACF RESNAMES WHICH FAILED RULES CHECKS
//RESRULES   DD *          * RACF BASE RENAME RULES
*
* DEFINE RULES FOR RESNAME PROFILES RECORD TYPE 0500
* +OPTIONS SPECIFIES THE DEFAULT VALUES TO BE ASSIGNED IF
*  NO RULE DOES MATCH
*
*
+OPTIONS     SET_OWNER=SGRESOWN,SET_UACC=ALTER
+RESNAME_RULE NAME='RA2002 RULE           ',
             CLASS=FACILITY,RESNAME=RA2*.**,OWNER=*,
             SET_OWNER=SETGOWNR,SET_UACC=READ
+RESNAME_RULE NAME='THIS IS A DATASET TES2',
             RESNAME=XRZP00?.**,OWNER=*,
             SET_OWNER=NEWOWNER,SET_UACC=ALTER
+RESNAME_RULE NAME='BAD OWNER AND OR  UACC',
             RESNAME=**,OWNER=OWN*,UACC=NONE,
             SET_OWNER=NEWOWNER,SET_UACC=NONE
/*
